What if kingdoms formed in Minecraft? In this video, we investigate this question by simulating civilization in the medieval times with peasants and vikings! Join My Discord! https://discord.com/invite/bcBHkZ2 Events Streamed on Twitch: https://twitch.tv/MagicGumLIVE Patreon for Maps and Event Priority! https://www.patreon.com/magicgum #Minecraft #Simulation #Civilization #Sociology #Medieval 100 players are dropped into different biomes with a unique specialty to encourage trade and diplomacy between civilizations. We’ve also added proximity chat to simulate realistic human interactions. In true medieval fashion, lawless vikings are scattered throughout the land, putting pressure on nations to cooperate. Each region tests how a society would develop with their own strengths and weaknesses. Will people form an empire or will the regions plunge into anarchy? This is Simulating Kingdoms in Minecraft, a variation of 100 Players Simulate Civilization in Minecraft! Everything from the primitive caveman beginnings to allied kingdoms fighting to the death will be covered. This will truly test the theories of what if everyone was trapped in minecraft, with more nuanced interactions. A lot of planning went into this video! Big thank you to everyone who helped with the event and video. The style of this video is similar to Primer, Wilbur Soot in parts. A large influence on this series has come from content creators like @Primer and @Wilbur Soot . Shoutout to these LEGENDS for letting me use their POVs! Go check them out! @Beastow (Twitch) @ClownPierce CTKiwi#6313 for the MagicCry Emote I’m back. Hope you enjoyed the video! Leave a like and subscribe if you want to see more videos like this :)

Description

What if kingdoms formed in Minecraft? In this video, we investigate this question by simulating civilization in the medieval times with peasants and vikings! Join My Discord! https://discord.com/invite/bcBHkZ2 Events Streamed on Twitch: https://twitch.tv/MagicGumLIVE Patreon for Maps and Event Priority! https://www.patreon.com/magicgum #Minecraft #Simulation #Civilization #Sociology #Medieval 100 players are dropped into different biomes with a unique specialty to encourage trade and diplomacy between civilizations. We’ve also added proximity chat to simulate realistic human interactions. In true medieval fashion, lawless vikings are scattered throughout the land, putting pressure on nations to cooperate. Each region tests how a society would develop with their own strengths and weaknesses. Will people form an empire or will the regions plunge into anarchy? This is Simulating Kingdoms in Minecraft, a variation of 100 Players Simulate Civilization in Minecraft! Everything from the primitive caveman beginnings to allied kingdoms fighting to the death will be covered. This will truly test the theories of what if everyone was trapped in minecraft, with more nuanced interactions. A lot of planning went into this video! Big thank you to everyone who helped with the event and video. The style of this video is similar to Primer, Wilbur Soot in parts. A large influence on this series has come from content creators like @Primer and @Wilbur Soot . Shoutout to these LEGENDS for letting me use their POVs! Go check them out! @Beastow (Twitch) @ClownPierce CTKiwi#6313 for the MagicCry Emote I’m back. Hope you enjoyed the video! Leave a like and subscribe if you want to see more videos like this :)
